    "plan_content": "Here's the full plan I've developed after thoroughly reading all relevant source files:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats`\n\n**8 files to touch, 2 new files to create.** Every step mirrors the existing `uv cache size` pattern.\n\n### Key findings from codebase exploration\n\n- `CacheBucket::iter()` in `crates/uv-cache/src/lib.rs` already enumerates all 10 standard buckets (`wheels-v6`, `sdists-v9`, `flat-index-v2`, `git-v0`, `interpreter-v4`, `simple-v21`, `archive-v0`, `builds-v0`, `environments-v2`, `binaries-v0`). Note: `Python` is intentionally excluded from `iter()` by convention.\n- `cache_size.rs` uses `diskus::DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()` — we reuse this for per-bucket sizes.\n- `Display for CacheBucket` calls the private `to_str()`, so `bucket.to_string()` gives the directory name without any visibility hack.\n- `human_readable_bytes()` from `uv-console` is already re-exported at `commands::human_readable_bytes`.\n- The `PreviewFeature` bitflags enum has slots up to `1 << 27` — we add `CacheStats = 1 << 28`.\n\n### Steps\n\n| # | File | What |\n|---|------|------|\n| 1 | `crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs` | Add `CacheStats = 1 << 28`, its `as_str()` → `\"cache-stats\"`, its `FromStr` arm |\n| 2 | `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs` | Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to `CacheCommand`; add `StatsArgs { human: bool }` struct (identical shape to `SizeArgs`) |\n| 3 | `crates/uv/src/lib.rs` | Add dispatch arm for `CacheCommand::Stats` → `commands::cache_stats(...)` |\n| 4 | `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs` | **New** — iterate `CacheBucket::iter()`, call `DiskUsage` per bucket, print aligned table with separator + total |\n| 5 | `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs` | `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` + `mod cache_stats;` |\n| 6 | `crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs` | Add `cache_stats()` command builder + `with_filtered_cache_stats()` snapshot filter helper |\n| 7 | `crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs` | **New** — 3 integration tests (empty, raw bytes, human-readable), snapshots populated via `UPDATE_EXPECT=1` |\n| 8 | `crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs` | `#[cfg(all(feature = \"test-python\", feature = \"test-pypi\"))] mod cache_stats;` |\n\n### Expected output (`--human`)\n```\nwheels-v6        1.2MiB\nsdists-v9        384.0KiB\nflat-index-v2    12.3KiB\ngit-v0           0.0B\ninterpreter-v4   4.2KiB\nsimple-v21       56.7KiB\narchive-v0       2.1MiB\nbuilds-v0        0.0B\nenvironments-v2  0.0B\nbinaries-v0      0.0B\n--------------------\nTotal            3.8MiB\n```",
